&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Tucson looks to Hydras with a stern expression.  He then back at Rodimus.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;So you chose to continue.  Good, this time try to refrain from making snide
&gt; comments.  AND HYDRAS, IF YOU SO MUCH AS TURN ON ANY OF US THIS ALLIANCE IS
&gt; OVER!  AM I UNDERSTOOD!?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He gives him a serious glare.

&lt;NEW&gt;

For a moment RODIMUS just stopped as TUSCON spoke and then turned and
looked at him, his face a soldier&#39;s face. &quot;We will talk later.&quot; And
then he turned back to continue on his path, shifting into his
vehicular mode as he moved.

Above him CYCLONUS floated, a large jet, his wings positioned for
atmospheric flight. &quot;If it means anything you were not given a
warrior&#39;s chance in battle.&quot; CYCLONUS said quietly to RODIMUS, &quot;That
was wrong. If we fight, it will not be from a stab in the back or a
reprogramming, it will be machine to machine weapon to weapon.&quot;

There was a grunt from RODIMUS, &quot;You know Cyclonus, I almost look
foward to that.&quot;

The two drove on, trying to find a way for mortal enemies to work together.
&gt; &lt;OLD &lt;Tuscon&gt;
&gt;
&gt; STAND BY ALL SOLDIERS!  DEPLOYING SONAR ATTACK AT FULL STRENGTH!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; With a deep breath, Tucson rattles the horizon with a sensor splitting sonic
&gt; inhibited roar.  A wave of sonar energy is cast from his throat and powerful
&gt; vocalizers.  Sharp teeth and fangs glimmer in the moonlight as a strong
&gt; silver tail thrashes the ground beneath his four feet.

As TUSCON&#39;s warning is heard the Predacons shift their audio circuits
off as they glance back at at the large dragon.

&gt;&gt;&gt;RRROOOAAARRR!!!&lt;&lt;&lt;

TUSCON&#39;s roar can be heard for hundreds of miles as the sound of it
echoes and re-echoes out across the miles and miles of dead dinosaurs.
One of the first things he reailzes is that although capable of large
amounts of damage, It is rougher and cruder in its sensory mode, but
capable of far more damage then he could once deliver before.

It is almost like a wind has picked up and blown some of the bodies
back. Dinosaurs that are caught in the cone of effect are broken and
tossed about, bones vibrating and then snapped as if hit by a tidal
wave, although instead of one of water, this one is made of sound.

No, it was not the same as his original sonar, but it was very effective indeed!

Around TUSCON the Predacons, as well as probrably the Maximals leaped
out of the way as the cones sweeps through. At high enough levels
sound can do actual physical damage and not just bust ear drums and
over load audio circuits.

As the roar dies down, the damage that is done is incredible and
TUSCON&#39;s energy cells are slowly trying to recharge themselves from
such a high energy output (OOC: He has to catch his breath). Across
the sensors there is no evidence of anyone being affected beyond the
dead dinosaurs and the movement of TUSCON&#39;s allies.

As far as anyone could tell either their enemy was out of range of
TUSCON&#39;s roar or was protected by them in some manner.

&quot;That was interesting.&quot; SKY SHADOW said from his position next to
HYDRAS as he shrugged his shoulders.

&quot;And loud!&quot; INJECTOR said as he buzzed near by. He was in beast mode
looking like a strange cross of lionfish and hornet.

CYCLONUS and RODIMUS continued up towards the path of devastation left
by the dinosaurs, RODIMUS weaving between the bodies in vehicle mode
while CYCLONUS just flew above them as a jet.

